# UI Theme Compatibility

For user-facing UI work, ensure visuals and states remain usable in both light and dark mode.

## Implementation guidance

- Avoid hardcoded one-theme-only colors for text, backgrounds, borders, and state highlights.
- Prefer semantic or theme-aware color tokens that can map cleanly to both themes.
- Maintain readable contrast for normal, hover, selected, disabled, warning, and error states.
- Ensure icons, badges, and status indicators stay recognizable on light and dark surfaces.

## Validation expectations

- When UI code changes, verify affected views in both light and dark mode before considering the task complete.
- If dual-theme validation cannot be run, explicitly note that gap in the completion summary.
